Notes on chess

Chess Class
	playGame()
		main method where everything starts
		creates board
		
	move()
		facilitates move
		calls an input method getMove()
		once move is received, calls move method specific for that piece
	validateMove()
		check if piece would land outside border or on top of piece of 
		same color
	pawnMove() queenMove() kingMove() ...
		validates specific move for each piece
	printBoard()
		prints "|" and "_" to make board
		each piece is just a char 'p' 'k' ...
	checkMate()
		checks if king is checked by any piece, if so, calls checkCheckMate
		if king is not checked, makes sure there is at least one possible
		move where king would not be in check